This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Machine Learning (ML) as it proposes a novel bidirectional dependency tree network to extract dependency structure features from sentences for aspect term extraction, which is a subtask in aspect-based sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and ML research. The paper also uses BiLSTM plus CRF, which are popular ML techniques used in NLP tasks. Hence, cs.LG (Learning) is the second likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of deep learning models, which is a common technique in AI research, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of information retrieval techniques, which is covered in cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which is covered in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
